The paper deals with the problem of sparse reconstruction, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Hadamard matrices is also related to topics in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS). The paper also involves techniques from machine learning and optimization (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
